{"id":2978,"date":"2022-12-19T13:31:26","date_gmt":"2022-12-19T12:31:26","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/?p=2978"},"modified":"2022-12-19T13:31:45","modified_gmt":"2022-12-19T12:31:45","slug":"triple-and-openaire-sign-memorandum-of-understanding","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/2022\/12\/triple-and-openaire-sign-memorandum-of-understanding\/","title":{"rendered":"TRIPLE and OpenAIRE sign Memorandum of Understanding"},"content":{"rendered":"<div id=\"modal-ready\">\n<p>A new collaboration between the OpenAIRE and TRIPLE teams aims to select through the Research Graph a vast number of open scholarly SSH resources, such as research data and publications and include them in the GoTriple platform.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><br>As both projects share open data management practices, the <a href=\"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/MoU-TRIPLE-and-OpenAIRE-NEXUS_signedYI.pdf\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/MoU-TRIPLE-and-OpenAIRE-NEXUS_signedYI.pdf\">Memorandum of Understanding<\/a> is a further step in the collaboration of both projects, aiming to strengthen key values OpenAIRE and the TRIPLE project share.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>&#8220;This MoU is a step more in the fruitful collaborations between OPERAS and OpenAIRE; especially in the perspective of publishing qualitative research outputs to facilitate their discovery and the building of cooperation all over Europe and across disciplines.&#8221;&nbsp;<\/p><p><strong>Suzanne Dumouchel<\/strong>,&nbsp;TRIPLE&nbsp;Project &amp; Scientific Coordinator<\/p><\/blockquote>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>&#8220;This collaboration enlightens the Social Science and Humanities scholarly resources from the OpenAIRE Research Graph in the GoTriple&nbsp;platform.&nbsp; We together envision a hub where researchers can better access larger research contents and reuse them, increasing the SSH community collaboration. Commitment, action, and change towards multilingualism and inclusivity of different types of research products are of key value for OpenAIRE&#8221;&nbsp;<\/p><p><strong>Natalia Manola<\/strong>, OpenAIRE CEO&nbsp;<\/p><\/blockquote>\n\n\n\n<p>OpenAIRE and TRIPLE will jointly work to make more research products openly available, striving to further fulfil Open Science ambitions.<\/p>\n<\/div>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>A new collaboration between the OpenAIRE and TRIPLE teams aims to select through the Research Graph a vast number of open scholarly SSH resources, such as research data and publications and include them in the GoTriple platform. As both projects<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":13,"featured_media":2979,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[1],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/2978"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/13"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=2978"}],"version-history":[{"count":2,"href":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/2978\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":2983,"href":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/2978\/revisions\/2983"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/2979"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=2978"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=2978"},{"taxonomy":"post_ta